Reasoning: The paper deals with formalising the pi-calculus, which is a topic in theoretical computer science. The use of logical frameworks and mechanised metatheory systems suggests a focus on formal methods and logic, which aligns with the cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) sub-category. The use of dependently-typed syntax and the exploration of concurrent transitions and causal equivalence of traces suggest a focus on programming languages and semantics, which aligns with the cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-categories. The paper also deals with bisimulation and structural congruence, which are topics in formal language theory, aligning with the cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents proofs of the diamond lemma, which is a topic in mathematical logic, aligning with the cs.THEORY (Theoretical Computer Science) sub-category.
